        <!-- ── Quick-start ── -->
        <p class="section-label">Quick Start</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Load &amp; plot a recording</h2>

        <div class="quickstart">
            <p>
                Use <code>utils.data_loader</code> to inspect any saved HDF5 file
                without launching the GUI.
            </p>
            <pre><span class="kw">from</span> utils.data_loader <span class="kw">import</span> load_hdf5, plot_data

<span class="cm"># Load raw data into a dict</span>
d = <span class="fn">load_hdf5</span>(<span class="st">"recording_2025-06-01.h5"</span>)
<span class="nb">print</span>(d[<span class="st">'channel_names'</span>])   <span class="cm"># ['Im (pA)', 'Vm (mV)', ...]</span>
<span class="nb">print</span>(d[<span class="st">'data'</span>].shape)       <span class="cm"># (n_channels, n_samples)</span>

<span class="cm"># Plot first 10 seconds, one subplot per channel</span>
<span class="fn">plot_data</span>(<span class="st">"recording_2025-06-01.h5"</span>, time_range=(<span class="nb">0</span>, <span class="nb">10</span>))</pre>
        </div>

        <hr class="section-divider">

        <!-- ── QC quick-start ── -->
        <p class="section-label">Quality Control</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Re-run QC or run alignment</h2>

        <div class="quickstart">
            <p>
                QC runs automatically after every save. To re-run it on an existing file,
                or to run the standalone hardware-alignment check, use these CLI entry points.
            </p>
            <pre><span class="cm"># Re-run the full post-recording QC pipeline on an existing file</span>
<span class="kw">from</span> analysis.qc.report <span class="kw">import</span> run_qc
result = <span class="fn">run_qc</span>(<span class="st">"recording_2025-06-01.h5"</span>)
<span class="nb">print</span>(result[<span class="st">'status'</span>])      <span class="cm"># 'pass', 'warn', or 'fail'</span>
<span class="nb">print</span>(result[<span class="st">'html_path'</span>])   <span class="cm"># path to the generated HTML report</span>

<span class="cm"># Standalone hardware alignment (run with Axon Patch-1U model cell)</span>
<span class="cm"># python -m analysis.qc_alignment --save-dir D:/data</span>
<span class="cm"># python -m analysis.qc_alignment --save-dir D:/data --no-phase-b</span></pre>
        </div>

        <hr class="section-divider">

        <!-- ── Key concepts ── -->
        <p class="section-label">Concepts</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Domain &amp; design notes</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">
            Refer to <a href="config.html"><code>config</code></a> for all
            physical-unit definitions and channel scaling.
        </p>

        <div class="feature-grid">
            <div class="feature-card">
                <div class="feature-card-title">Current Clamp (CC)</div>
                <div class="feature-card-body">
                    Inject current in pA; record membrane voltage in mV.
                    AO scale: <strong>400 pA/V</strong> — write X/400 V to ao0
                    to inject X pA.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-card">
                <div class="feature-card-title">Voltage Clamp (VC)</div>
                <div class="feature-card-body">
                    Command voltage in mV; record clamping current in pA.
                    AO scale: <strong>20 mV/V</strong> — write X/20 V for X mV command.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-card">
                <div class="feature-card-title">TTL Synchronization</div>
                <div class="feature-card-body">
                    5 V pulses via counter task on <code>PFI12</code>. Triggers
                    Basler camera on Line1 — phase-locked to acquisition.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-card">
                <div class="feature-card-title">Trial State Machine</div>
                <div class="feature-card-body">
                    IDLE &rarr; ITI &rarr; PRE &rarr; TRIAL &rarr; DONE.
                    Staircase amplitudes step automatically across the protocol.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-card">
                <div class="feature-card-title">Clock Topology</div>
                <div class="feature-card-body">
                    AI task = master clock. AO slaved via
                    <code>ai/SampleClock</code>. CTR runs from the 100 MHz
                    on-board timebase.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-card">
                <div class="feature-card-title">HDF5 Layout</div>
                <div class="feature-card-body">
                    <code>/data/analog_input</code> — float64 (n_ch &times; n_samp),
                    LZF compressed. Full metadata in <code>/metadata</code> group.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-card">
                <div class="feature-card-title">Post-recording QC</div>
                <div class="feature-card-body">
                    Automatic background QC after every save: sample-count consistency,
                    finite values, stimulus events, TTL&nbsp;&harr;&nbsp;video frame-count drift,
                    and an interactive plotly channel overview.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="feature-card">
                <div class="feature-card-title">Hardware Alignment</div>
                <div class="feature-card-body">
                    Weekly rig check via <code>python -m analysis.qc_alignment</code>.
                    Phase A (no model cell): loopback latency, crosstalk, TTL jitter.
                    Phase B (Axon Patch-1U, 500 MΩ): CC/VC scaling, noise, τ.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

